    "plan_content": "Here's the full implementation plan:\n\n---\n\n## Plan Summary\n\n### What gets created\n- **2 new files** — component + demo\n- **2 registry inserts** — append-only, no existing file modifications except registry arrays\n\n### Architecture\n\nThe Stepper uses **two nested React contexts** (same pattern as `carousel.tsx`):\n\n1. **`StepperContext`** (root) — `activeStep` + `orientation`\n2. **`StepperItemContext`** (item) — `step` + computed `state` (`\"completed\" | \"active\" | \"pending\"`)\n\nEach context has a guard hook (`useStepper()`, `useStepperItem()`) that throws a descriptive error when used outside its provider.\n\n### 7 exported components\n\n| Component | Element | Key behavior |\n|-----------|---------|--------------|\n| `Stepper` | `<div>` | Provides StepperContext; flex layout switches by orientation |\n| `StepperItem` | `<div>` | Computes state from `step` vs `activeStep`; provides StepperItemContext |\n| `StepperTrigger` | `<button>` | Shows step number by default; styled differently per state |\n| `StepperTitle` | `<p>` | Simple label |\n| `StepperDescription` | `<p>` | Muted secondary text |\n| `StepperSeparator` | `<div>` | Inside StepperItem as last child; `bg-primary` when state=completed, `bg-muted` otherwise |\n| `StepperContent` | `<div>` | Returns `null` unless `step === activeStep` |\n\n### Separator design decision\n`StepperSeparator` lives **inside `<StepperItem>`** (last child). `StepperItem` is `flex flex-row`, so the separator naturally stretches horizontally to fill space between the trigger-group and the next item. It reads `state` from `StepperItemContext` and `orientation` from `StepperContext`.\n\n### Demo\n3-step stepper (Account → Profile → Complete) with `useState(1)` for active step, clickable triggers, Previous/Next buttons with boundary guards, and swappable content panels via `StepperContent`.\n\n### No external dependencies\nPure React + Tailwind — no new npm packages in the registry entry.",
